### TKT-005 — Infinite redirect loop on nethealth.example.com

**Symptom:** `curl -IL https://nethealth.example.com` returns `Maximum (50) redirects followed`.

**Cause:** Nginx port 80 block had `return 301 https://$host$request_uri`. Cloudflare sends HTTP to the tunnel, Nginx redirects to HTTPS, Cloudflare receives the redirect and sends HTTP again — infinite loop.

**Cause of confusion:** Standard Nginx SSL setup includes this redirect. It is incorrect for Cloudflare Tunnel setups because Cloudflare handles HTTP→HTTPS at the edge. The tunnel always delivers HTTP to Nginx internally.

**Resolution:** Removed the port 80 redirect block entirely. Cloudflare's Always Use HTTPS setting handles the redirect at the edge.

