### TKT-006 — All client IPs showing as 127.0.0.1 in Nginx logs

**Symptom:** Nginx error log shows `client: 127.0.0.1` for all requests. Rate limiting and fail2ban track all users as the same IP.

**Cause:** Cloudflare Tunnel runs on the same machine and forwards requests from localhost. Nginx sees the tunnel's local address, not the real visitor IP. The real IP is passed in the `X-Forwarded-For` header by Cloudflare but Nginx was not configured to use it.

**Resolution:** Added to both Nginx server blocks:

```nginx
set_real_ip_from 127.0.0.1;
real_ip_header X-Forwarded-For;
```

Also added `allow 127.0.0.1` to the Cloudflare IP whitelist so the tunnel is not blocked before real IP resolution occurs.

