### TKT-007 — Direct LAN IP access returning 200

**Symptom:** 
returns 200 OK — bypasses Cloudflare.

**Cause:** Nginx default site (`/etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default`) was still active, catching all requests that don't match a server_name.

**Resolution:**

1. Removed default site: `sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default`
2. Added `default_server` catch-all block returning 444 (no response) for direct IP access

**Scope note:** On CGNAT, no external traffic can reach the server directly since there is no public IP. The LAN bypass is a local network issue only — not an internet-facing exposure.

